2 party; and
3 2. Five members of the Oklahoma House of Representatives to be
4 appointed by the Speaker of the House of Representatives. Four of
5 the members shall be from the majority party and one member shall be
6 from the minority party.
7 B. The chairman and vice-chairman of the Committee shall be
8 designated from the membership of the Committee by the Speaker of
9 the House of Representatives and the President Pro Tempore of the
10 Senate as provided for in this subsection. The President Pro
11 Tempore of the Senate shall designate the initial chairman who shall
12 serve until the convening of the First Regular Session of the 61st
13 Oklahoma Legislature. The Speaker of the House of Representatives
14 shall designate the initial vice-chairman who shall serve until the
