17 SECTION 7. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 91.7d of Title 20, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. Except as provided in subsection B of this section, actions
21 shall be brought before the business court as follows:
22 1. An action within the jurisdiction of the business court may
23 be filed in the business court. The filing party shall plead facts
24 sufficient to establish venue in a county in a division of the
ENGR. H. B. NO. 1562 Page 15

1 busi ness court. Venue may be established as provided by law or, if
2 a written contract specifies a county as venue for the action, as
3 provided by the contract;
4 2. If the business court determines it does not have
5 jurisdiction over the action, the business court shall:
6 a. transfer the action to a district court in a county
7 with jurisdiction over the action, or
8 b. dismiss the action without prejudice to the rights of
9 the parties; and
10 3. If the business court determines that the venue is improper
11 as to the action, the business court shall transfer the action to
12 the court of proper venue.
13 B. 1. A district court in this state may transfer an action to
14 the business court division of proper venue if the district court
15 judge determines the business court has subject matter jurisdiction
16 over the action.
17 2. A party to an action filed in a district court that is
18 within the jurisdiction of the business court may remove the action
19 to the business court. If the business court does not have
20 jurisdiction of the action, the business court shall remand the
21 action to the court in which the action was originally filed.
22 C. A party to an action filed in a district court of proper
23 venue that is not within an operating division of the business
24
