3 SECTION 8. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 91.7e of Title 20, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 Nonjury trials in a business court shall be resolved within
7 twelve (12) months of the filing of the action. The twelve-month
8 disposition schedule may be extended if both parties agree to a
9 longer resolution period. Such an extension shall be agreed upon in
10 writing by all parties and approved by the court.
